# ==================== POLICY: Code Review Requirements ====================
#
# MANDATORY for all PRs:
#
# Phase 1 (Design):
#   - Required for: Feature flags, new APIs, architectural changes, breaking changes
#   - Skip for: Bug fixes, documentation-only, tests-only, refactoring (zero behavior change)
#   - Deliverable: ADR (Architecture Decision Record) linked in PR
#
# Phase 2 (Code):
#   - Required for: ALL changes
#   - 2 senior engineer approvals mandatory
#   - Checklist: Security, testing, observability, deployment readiness
#   - Status: Automated via pr-quality-gates.yml workflow
#
# Phase 3 (Operations):
#   - Required for: Infrastructure changes, deployment procedure changes
#   - Reviewer: On-call SRE or operations engineer
#   - Deliverable: Load test results, rollback validation
#
# Phase 4 (Production):
#   - Required for: ALL changes to main branch
#   - Final sign-off by: On-call engineer
#   - Post-deployment: 1-hour monitoring by PR author
#
# RULE: Self-reviews do NOT count (your approval doesn't approve your own code)